# HawkView backend — cursor rules
# Always active. Read before every task.

## Project
NestJS monorepo at apps/api. PostgreSQL + Prisma. pnpm workspaces.
This is a solo part-time project. Autonomous, careful progress is the goal.

## Stack
- Runtime: Node.js, NestJS (feature modules)
- DB: PostgreSQL via Docker, Prisma ORM (client output: src/generated/prisma)
- Auth: JWT in httpOnly cookies (access + refresh tokens)
- Package manager: pnpm
- Testing: Jest
- API: REST, JSON responses shaped as { success: true, data: {} }

## Folder layout
apps/api/src/
  auth/           # JWT auth, login, register, refresh, logout
  users/          # User CRUD (Prisma only in service)
  tenants/        # Connected M365 tenants
  microsoft/      # Graph API client, OAuth flow
  health/         # GET /health — always keep working
  prisma/         # PrismaService (global singleton)
  common/         # Shared filters, guards, decorators, utils
  config/         # app.config.ts + env.validation.ts
  generated/      # Prisma client output — never edit manually

## Architecture rules — non-negotiable
- Controllers are thin: validate input, call service, return response. No business logic.
- Services own all business logic. Prisma is only called inside services.
- Never call PrismaService from a controller.
- Every module imports only what it needs. No circular deps.
- Multi-tenant safety: every DB query that touches tenant data MUST be scoped by tenantId.
  Never return data across tenants. This is a hard security requirement.
- Auth: JWT lives in httpOnly cookie named access_token. Never put tokens in response body.
  Refresh token stored in DB (RefreshToken model), rotated on every use.
- Env vars: always access via ConfigService, never process.env directly (except main.ts bootstrap).

## Response format
All endpoints return:
  { success: true, data: { ... } }       # success
  { success: false, code: 'ERROR_CODE', message: 'Human readable' }  # error

Error codes are SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE strings. Use HttpException with this shape.
Global exception filter (common/filters/api-exception.filter.ts) handles unhandled errors.

## Prisma rules
- Schema: apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma
- Connection URL lives in apps/api/prisma.config.ts (Prisma 7 rejects
  `url = env("DATABASE_URL")` in schema.prisma with P1012).
- After any schema change: run migration, then regenerate client
  pnpm --filter api prisma migrate dev --name <description>
  pnpm --filter api prisma generate
- Never edit src/generated/prisma manually.

## Current auth state (phase 1 complete)
- POST /auth/register  — creates user, sets access_token + refresh_token cookies
- POST /auth/login     — validates credentials, sets both cookies
- GET  /auth/me        — returns current user (JwtAuthGuard)
- POST /auth/refresh   — rotates refresh token, issues new access_token
- POST /auth/logout    — revokes refresh token row, clears both cookies
- 15-min access JWT, 7-day opaque refresh token (SHA-256 hash in DB,
  single-session, rotation on use).
- Global ThrottlerModule: 100 req/min default, 10 req/min on
  /auth/login and /auth/register.
- Swagger UI at /docs, OpenAPI JSON at /docs-json.

