## Coding rules
- Small, focused changes only. One concern per PR/commit.
- No massive refactors unless explicitly instructed.
- No placeholder logic — if it's not implemented, don't commit it as if it is.
- No console.log in committed code. Use NestJS Logger.
- Always use async/await, never .then() chains.
- DTOs use class-validator decorators. Always validate request bodies.
- Types over any. No implicit any.

## Testing rules
- Services: unit test with Jest + mocked PrismaService
- Critical endpoints: e2e test with supertest
- If skipping a test, add a comment explaining why and create a TODO
- Run before every commit: pnpm --filter api test && pnpm --filter api build

## Definition of done — a task is NOT done unless
- [ ] pnpm --filter api build passes
- [ ] pnpm --filter api test passes
- [ ] No broken imports
- [ ] Migrations applied + prisma generated (if schema changed)
- [ ] Endpoint manually verified (curl or /docs Swagger UI)
- [ ] No placeholder or commented-out logic committed

## Setup verification (run if anything feels broken)
pnpm install
docker compose up -d        # starts postgres
pnpm --filter api prisma migrate deploy
pnpm --filter api prisma generate
pnpm --filter api start:dev
curl http://localhost:3000/health   # must return { status: 'ok' }

## Commit format
feat(scope): what was added
fix(scope): what was fixed
refactor(scope): what was restructured
test(scope): what was tested
chore(scope): tooling/config change

Scopes: auth | users | tenants | microsoft | prisma | health | common | config
